    <center><table class="itemDisplayTable">
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Title:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Time Synchronization for Road Traffic Monitoring System in Wireless Multimedia Sensor Networks</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Authors:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Durgadevi G</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Keywords:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Time Synchronization<br />Road Traffic Monitoring System<br />Wireless Multimedia Sensor Networks</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Issue Date:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">May-2010 </td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Publisher:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">SRM University</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Series/Report no.:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">P5215</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Abstract:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Multimedia surveillance sensor networks have been used for Storage of potentially relevant activities. Multimedia sensors could infer and record potentially relevant activities like thefts, car accidents, traffic violations and make video/audio streams or reports available for future query and used for Traffic avoidance, enforcement and control systems. Sensors could also detect violations and transmit video streams to law enforcement agencies to identify the violator, or buffer images and streams in case of accidents for subsequent accident scene analysis.
As Time synchronization is essential for distributed networks to realize certain functionality such as real-time event management and system monitoring in WSN,I want to incorporate time synchronization using TOA in on road traffic monitoring to avoid accidents, considering cases where sensors are deployed in a dense fashion. When an event happens multiple sensors that observe the phenomena may report at the same time. With synchronized clocks, redundant messages can be recognized and suppressed to save energy by reducing unnecessary data traffic across the sensor networks.
A road traffic monitoring system includes:
- The input for receiving position estimations of mobile terminals; [on road vehicles]
- An output for generating road traffic maps, to avoid accidents.
Operators of remote video surveillance systems require robust, high-speed, high Bandwidth network connections to each remote camera. If choosing a wireless solution to support their surveillance system, it must be rugged and robust enough to operate in all weather conditions and must deliver consistent predictable performance equivalent to wire line systems. Any compromise will lead to degraded quality of the real-time video and may even render deployed systems unusable.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">URI:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/10357">http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/10357</a></td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Appears in Collections:</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="/dspace/handle/123456789/9818">CSE-2010</a><br/></td></tr>
</table></center><br/>
